message.content: cs.IT, cs.IT is the most likely category as the paper deals with information theory and coding theorems. Other likely categories could be cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) as the paper deals with the distribution of information in a sequence, cs.DM (discrete mathematics) as the paper deals with entropy and information spectrum, cs.LG (machine learning) as the paper deals with information and probability, and cs.CC (computational complexity) as the paper deals with the tradeoff between rate and error probability.
